weak as is a slave."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wagada","text_ar":"وَغَدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawoma","text_ar":"القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagidu","text_ar":"يَغِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wagodN","text_ar":"وَغْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He served the people; acted as a servant to them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L.)"}],"source_refs":["L","Msb","K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n42144","headword_ar":"وَغْدٌ","root":"wgd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignoble, mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sordid, and weak person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who serves for the food of his belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stupid, weak"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in intellect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignoble, and mean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sordid:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak in body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light in intellect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak; as is a slave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Umm-El-Heythem, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who eats and carries away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Expos. of the Lámeeyeh of Et-Tughráee.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A servant of a people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slave."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A boy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K.) ―         -b5-  Pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awogaAdN","text_ar":"اَوْغَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wugodaAnN","text_ar":"وُغْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wagodaAnN","text_ar":"وَغْدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain arrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of those used in the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to which no portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"share, pertains."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K.) Accord. to the A, this is the original signification. (TA.) ―         -b7-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fruit of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baA*inojaAn","text_ar":"بَاذِنْجَان"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuwaAgadapu","text_ar":"المُوَاغَدَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain game"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Arabs, in which one player does like as the other does."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b9-  See also 3."}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","L","K"]}]}}